# @boaideas/ui-kit — Adding New Components

## 1. Where to place a component

| Type | Location |
|------|----------|
| New React component (any complexity) | `src/components/<Name>/` — React + TSX + CVA + Tailwind |
| Legacy Vue primitive (Text, Tag) | `src/primitives/` — `<style lang="scss">` only |
| Legacy Vue interactive (Modal, Tooltip) | `src/patterns/` — Tailwind + Reka UI |
| Business-domain atoms/molecules | `domain-level/entity/<domain>/ui/<Name>/` |
| Business-domain composite widgets | `domain-level/widgets/<Name>/` |

## 2. React Component Folder Structure

```
src/components/<ComponentName>/
  <ComponentName>.tsx           ← component + types inline
  <ComponentName>.stories.ts    ← Storybook stories
```

- Types live **inline** in the `.tsx` file — no separate `types.ts` unless the types need to be exported for consumers.
- Always use `@/` alias: `import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'`.
- Use `cn()` (clsx + tailwind-merge) for all className composition.
- Use `cva` from `class-variance-authority` for variant logic.

### CVA pattern:
```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority'
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'

const componentVariants = cva('base-classes', {
  variants: {
    variant: {
      default: 'bg-brand text-text-on-brand hover:bg-brand-dark',
      outline: 'border border-border bg-surface hover:bg-surface-raised text-text',
      ghost:   'hover:bg-surface-raised text-text-muted',
      danger:  'bg-danger text-text-on-brand hover:opacity-90',
    },
    size: {
      sm: 'h-8 px-sm text-sm',
      md: 'h-10 px-md',
      lg: 'h-12 px-lg text-lg',
    },
  },
  defaultVariants: { variant: 'default', size: 'md' },
})

interface ComponentProps
  extends React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof componentVariants> {}
```

### shadcn → our tokens mapping (MANDATORY — never use shadcn defaults):
| shadcn class | our class |
|---|---|
| `bg-primary` | `bg-brand` |
| `text-primary-foreground` | `text-text-on-brand` |
| `bg-destructive` | `bg-danger` |
| `bg-background` | `bg-surface` |
| `bg-secondary` | `bg-surface-raised` |
| `text-foreground` | `text-text` |
| `text-muted-foreground` | `text-text-muted` |
| `bg-accent` (hover) | `bg-surface-raised` |
| `text-primary` (link) | `text-brand` |
| `border-input` | `border-border` |
| `ring-ring` | `ring-brand` |
| `fill-muted-foreground` | `fill-text-muted` |
| `fill-muted` | `fill-surface` |

## 3. Vue Component Folder Structure (legacy, Mandatory)

Every Vue component must reside in its own directory.

```
path/to/<ComponentName>/
  <ComponentName>.vue        ← component logic and template
  types.ts                  ← prop, emit, and translation interfaces
  index.ts                  ← clean exports (component + types)
  <ComponentName>.stories.ts ← (optional) Storybook stories
  assets/                   ← (optional) component-specific images/icons
```

### index.ts pattern:
```ts
export { default as <ComponentName> } from './<ComponentName>.vue';
export * from './types';
```

### types.ts guidelines:
- Name the file `types.ts` exactly.
- **Always use `@/` alias** for all imports — both in `.vue` files and `.ts` files (e.g., `import type { Price } from '@/domain-level/types'`). Never use deep relative paths like `../../../../types`.
- **No Duplication:** Do not redefine common interfaces (like `Price`, `Variant`). Import them from `@/domain-level/types`.
- **`tsconfig.build.json` must mirror the alias:** The build tsconfig must include `"baseUrl": "."` and `"paths": { "@/*": ["src/*"] }` so that `tsc -p tsconfig.build.json` can resolve `@/` in plain `.ts` files. Without this, `tsc` fails even though Vite and `vite-plugin-dts` handle it correctly via `vite.config.ts`.


## 3. Styling — NEVER use Bootstrap or hardcoded values

**No Bootstrap classes** (`d-flex`, `col-*`, `px-3`, `mb-2`, etc.) — use Tailwind utilities instead.
**No custom `@media` queries** in SCSS — use Tailwind breakpoints defined in `tailwind.preset.js` (e.g., `desktop:`).
- **Mobile First:** The default view is considered mobile up to `991px`.
- **Desktop Breakpoint:** From `992px` and above, the view is considered desktop. Use the `desktop:` prefix (e.g., `desktop:flex-row`).

| What | Do | Never |
|------|----|-------|
| Colors | `var(--primary-color-1)` or `text-primary-1` | `#002349` or Bootstrap `text-primary` |
| Spacing | `var(--spacing-m)` or Tailwind `p-m` | `16px` or Bootstrap `p-3` |
| Font size | `<Text variant="b2">` or `@include typo-b2` | `font-size: 16px` |
| Font weight | `var(--font-weight-semibold)` or `font-semibold` | `font-weight: 600` |
| Border radius | `var(--radius-md)` or `rounded-md` | `12px` |
| Transitions | `var(--transition-base)` or `duration-base` | `200ms` |
| Breakpoints | `desktop:max-w-[345px]` or `desktop:block` | `@media (min-width: 992px)` in `<style>` |

Tailwind is for **layout** (`flex`, `gap-s`, `px-m`, `items-center`).
SCSS mixins (`@include typo-b2`) are for **typography** in `<style>` blocks.

## 4. Token flow — single source of truth

```
src/tokens/palette.css        ← hex values ONLY here (--palette-*)
src/tokens/theme-light.css    ← semantic tokens (--color-*) for light theme
src/tokens/theme-dark.css     ← semantic tokens for dark theme (.dark selector)
src/spacing-variables.scss    ← spacing scale ONLY here
src/typography-variables.scss ← font sizes/weights ONLY here
src/styles/style.css          ← radius + transitions ONLY here
```

Never add raw values to `design-tokens.ts` or `ui/tokens/` — those files contain **type names only**.

## 5. API Design & Prop Naming

**State Props:** Avoid abstract names like `modelValue` for UI components (modals, alerts, dropdowns) unless it's a form input.
- **Do:** Use semantic names like `visible`, `isOpen`, `isActive` and emit matching events (`update:visible`).
- **Never:** Use `modelValue` for visibility toggles.

## 6. Text component API

```vue
<Text variant="b2" weight="semibold" color="primary-color-1" as="span">
  Label
</Text>
```

- `variant` → `h1–h4`, `s1–s2`, `b1–b3`, `body`, `caption`, `credit`
- `color` → any key from `src/ui/tokens/colors.ts` (e.g. `primary-color-1`, `grey-700`)
- `weight` → `light` | `regular` | `medium` | `semibold` | `bold`
- `as` → overrides HTML tag; use `as="span"` for inline, `as="s"` for strikethrough

Use `<Text>` for all visible text in domain-level components. Never use raw `<span>` or `<p>` with hardcoded styles.

## 6. ContentPlate

Use `ContentPlate` from `@/primitives/ContentPlate/ContentPlate.vue` as the card background.

Embed it **inside** the component when the card appearance is part of the component contract:

```vue
<ContentPlate>
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-s px-m py-s">
    <!-- content -->
  </div>
</ContentPlate>
```

## 7. Exports — mandatory after adding a component

1. Export from the relevant barrel — component default + named types:

```ts
// domain-level/widgets/index.ts
export * from './MyWidget';
```

2. Register in `install()` in `src/index.ts`:

```ts
app.component('MyWidget', MyWidget);
```

## 9. Stories structure & Documentation

Every component MUST have comprehensive documentation in its `.stories.ts` file via the `meta` object:
1. **Component Description:** Add `parameters.docs.description.component` explaining its purpose and responsive behavior.
2. **Prop Definitions:** Provide detailed descriptions in `argTypes`, categorized via `table.category` ('Data' | 'Appearance' | 'State').
3. **Events (Emits):** Document all emitted events in `argTypes` under the 'Emits' category. Include an `action` and specify the payload type using `table.type.summary` (e.g., `void`, `boolean`).
4. **Slots:** Document supported slots in `argTypes` under the 'Slots' category.

```ts
const meta: Meta<typeof MyWidget> = {
  title: 'Domain/Widgets/MyWidget',
  component: MyWidget,
  tags: ['autodocs'],
  decorators: [cardDecorator],
  parameters: {
    docs: {
      description: { component: 'Describe what it is and how it behaves responsively.' },
    },
  },
  argTypes: {
    visible: { 
      description: 'Controls component visibility.', 
      table: { category: 'State' } 
    },
    'onUpdate:visible': { 
      action: 'update:visible', 
      description: 'Fired on close.', 
      table: { category: 'Emits', type: { summary: 'boolean' } } 
    },
    default: { 
      description: 'Default content slot.', 
      table: { category: 'Slots', type: { summary: 'VNode | string' } } 
    }
  },
};
```

- One named export per meaningful state (e.g. `WithDiscount`, `NoDiscount`)
- JSDoc comment above each story explaining what it demonstrates
- All mock data in named constants at the top of the file (amounts in **cents/minor units**)
- `translations` object in a named `TRANSLATIONS` constant

## 10. Money formatting

Always use `moneyDisplay` from `@/domain-level/utils/money` — never format amounts manually.
All price values are in **minor units (cents)**: `1699` → `$16.99`.

## 11. What NOT to do

- ALL code comments MUST be in English
- Do not hardcode hex colors, px sizes, ms durations in `<style>` blocks
- Do not use Bootstrap (`d-flex`, `col-*`, `px-3`, `mb-2`, etc.) anywhere
- Do not add raw token values to `design-tokens.ts` or `ui/tokens/*.ts`
- Do not add font sizes in component CSS — use `@include typo-*`
- Do not add `reka-ui` to `peerDependencies` (it is intentionally bundled)
- Do not use `<span style="font-size: 14px">` — use `<Text variant="b3">`
